verses.text_plain: Say ye unto your brethren, Ammi; and to your sisters, Ru–hamah.
verses.verse_html:
1Say ye unto your brethren, Ammi; and to your sisters, Ru–hamah. ▼
▼ Ammi: that is, My people
 , ▼
▼ Ru–hamah: that is, Having obtained mercy

footnotes.body_html: ▼ Ammi: that is, My people

footnotes.body_text: ▼ Ru–hamah: that is, Having obtained mercy
footnotes.body_html: ▼ Ru–hamah: that is, Having obtained mercy

verses.text_plain: Plead with your mother, plead: for she is not my wife, neither am I her husband: let her therefore put away her whoredoms out of her sight, and her adulteries from between her breasts;
verses.verse_html: 2Plead with your mother, plead: for she is not my wife, neither am I her husband: let her therefore put away her whoredoms out of her sight, and her adulteries from between her breasts;

verses.text_plain: Lest I strip her naked, and set her as in the day that she was born, and make her as a wilderness, and set her like a dry land, and slay her with thirst.
verses.verse_html: 3Lest I strip her naked, and set her as in the day that she was born, and make her as a wilderness, and set her like a dry land, and slay her with thirst.

verses.text_plain: And I will not have mercy upon her children; for they be the children of whoredoms.
verses.verse_html: 4And I will not have mercy upon her children; for they be the children of whoredoms.

tokens.text: And I will not have mercy

verses.text_plain: For their mother hath played the harlot: she that conceived them hath done shamefully: for she said, I will go after my lovers, that give me my bread and my water, my wool and my flax, mine oil and my drink.
verses.verse_html:
5For their mother hath played the harlot: she that conceived them hath done shamefully: for she said, I will go after my lovers, that give me my bread and my water, my wool and my flax, mine oil and my drink. ▼
▼ drink: Heb. drinks

verses.text_plain: Therefore, behold, I will hedge up thy way with thorns, and make a wall, that she shall not find her paths.
verses.verse_html:
6Therefore, behold, I will hedge up thy way with thorns, and make a wall, that she shall not find her paths. ▼
▼ make…: Heb. wall a wall

footnotes.body_html: ▼ make…: Heb. wall a wall

verses.text_plain: And she shall follow after her lovers, but she shall not overtake them; and she shall seek them, but shall not find them: then shall she say, I will go and return to my first husband; for then was it better with me than now.
verses.verse_html: 7And she shall follow after her lovers, but she shall not overtake them; and she shall seek them, but shall not find them: then shall she say, I will go and return to my first husband; for then was it better with me than now.

verses.text_plain: For she did not know that I gave her corn, and wine, and oil, and multiplied her silver and gold, which they prepared for Baal.
verses.verse_html:
8For she did not know that I gave her corn, and wine, and oil, and multiplied her silver and gold, which they prepared for Baal. ▼
▼ wine: Heb. new wine
 , ▼
▼ which…: or, wherewith they made Baal

footnotes.body_html: ▼ wine: Heb. new wine

footnotes.body_text: ▼ which…: or, wherewith they made Baal
footnotes.body_html: ▼ which…: or, wherewith they made Baal

verses.text_plain: Therefore will I return, and take away my corn in the time thereof, and my wine in the season thereof, and will recover my wool and my flax given to cover her nakedness.
verses.verse_html:
9Therefore will I return, and take away my corn in the time thereof, and my wine in the season thereof, and will recover my wool and my flax given to cover her nakedness. ▼
▼ recover: or, take away

footnotes.body_html: ▼ recover: or, take away

verses.text_plain: And now will I discover her lewdness in the sight of her lovers, and none shall deliver her out of mine hand.
verses.verse_html:
10And now will I discover her lewdness in the sight of her lovers, and none shall deliver her out of mine hand. ▼
▼ lewdness: Heb. folly, or, villany

footnotes.body_html: ▼ lewdness: Heb. folly, or, villany

verses.text_plain: I will also cause all her mirth to cease, her feast days, her new moons, and her sabbaths, and all her solemn feasts.
verses.verse_html: 11I will also cause all her mirth to cease, her feast days, her new moons, and her sabbaths, and all her solemn feasts.

tokens.text: I will also cause all her mirth

verses.text_plain: And I will destroy her vines and her fig trees, whereof she hath said, These are my rewards that my lovers have given me: and I will make them a forest, and the beasts of the field shall eat them.
verses.verse_html:
12And I will destroy her vines and her fig trees, whereof she hath said, These are my rewards that my lovers have given me: and I will make them a forest, and the beasts of the field shall eat them. ▼
▼ destroy: Heb. make desolate

footnotes.body_html: ▼ destroy: Heb. make desolate

verses.text_plain: And I will visit upon her the days of Baalim, wherein she burned incense to them, and she decked herself with her earrings and her jewels, and she went after her lovers, and forgat me, saith the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 13And I will visit upon her the days of Baalim, wherein she burned incense to them, and she decked herself with her earrings and her jewels, and she went after her lovers, and forgat me, saith the Lord.

verses.text_plain: Therefore, behold, I will allure her, and bring her into the wilderness, and speak comfortably unto her.
verses.verse_html:
14Therefore, behold, I will allure her, and bring her into the wilderness, and speak comfortably unto her. ▼
▼ comfortably: or, friendly: Heb. to her heart

footnotes.body_text: ▼ comfortably: or, friendly: Heb. to her heart
footnotes.body_html: ▼ comfortably: or, friendly: Heb. to her heart

verses.text_plain: And I will give her her vineyards from thence, and the valley of Achor for a door of hope: and she shall sing there, as in the days of her youth, and as in the day when she came up out of the land of Egypt.
verses.verse_html: 15And I will give her her vineyards from thence, and the valley of Achor for a door of hope: and she shall sing there, as in the days of her youth, and as in the day when she came up out of the land of Egypt.

verses.text_plain: And it shall be at that day, saith the Lord, that thou shalt call me Ishi; and shalt call me no more Baali.
verses.verse_html:
16And it shall be at that day, saith the Lord, that thou shalt call me Ishi; and shalt call me no more Baali. ▼
▼ Ishi: that is, My husband
 , ▼
▼ Baali: that is, My lord

tokens.text: And it shall be at that day

footnotes.body_html: ▼ Ishi: that is, My husband
▼ Baali: that is, My lord

verses.text_plain: For I will take away the names of Baalim out of her mouth, and they shall no more be remembered by their name.
verses.verse_html: 17For I will take away the names of Baalim out of her mouth, and they shall no more be remembered by their name.

tokens.text: and they shall no more be remembered

verses.text_plain: And in that day will I make a covenant for them with the beasts of the field, and with the fowls of heaven, and with the creeping things of the ground: and I will break the bow and the sword and the battle out of the earth, and will make them to lie down safely.
verses.verse_html: 18And in that day will I make a covenant for them with the beasts of the field, and with the fowls of heaven, and with the creeping things of the ground: and I will break the bow and the sword and the battle out of the earth, and will make them to lie down safely.

tokens.text: and will make them to lie down

verses.text_plain: And I will betroth thee unto me for ever; yea, I will betroth thee unto me in righteousness, and in judgment, and in lovingkindness, and in mercies.
verses.verse_html: 19And I will betroth thee unto me for ever; yea, I will betroth thee unto me in righteousness, and in judgment, and in lovingkindness, and in mercies.

verses.text_plain: I will even betroth thee unto me in faithfulness: and thou shalt know the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 20I will even betroth thee unto me in faithfulness: and thou shalt know the Lord.

verses.text_plain: And it shall come to pass in that day, I will hear, saith the Lord, I will hear the heavens, and they shall hear the earth;
verses.verse_html: 21And it shall come to pass in that day, I will hear, saith the Lord, I will hear the heavens, and they shall hear the earth;

tokens.text: And it shall come to pass in that day

verses.text_plain: And the earth shall hear the corn, and the wine, and the oil; and they shall hear Jezreel.
verses.verse_html: 22And the earth shall hear the corn, and the wine, and the oil; and they shall hear Jezreel.

verses.text_plain: And I will sow her unto me in the earth; and I will have mercy upon her that had not obtained mercy; and I will say to them which were not my people, Thou art my people; and they shall say, Thou art my God.
verses.verse_html: 23And I will sow her unto me in the earth; and I will have mercy upon her that had not obtained mercy; and I will say to them which were not my people, Thou art my people; and they shall say, Thou art my God.

tokens.text: her unto me in the earth
upon her that had not obtained mercy
